projectInfo.name: Tanzania missing buildings Tanga West
projectInfo.shortDescription: Adding buildings to the OSM base map
projectInfo.description:
Tanzania has a very high incidence of Female Genital Mutilation, extreme poverty, early marriage and Gender Based Violence. NGOs on the ground need better maps to facilitate their outreach work and protect girls at risk of FGM.

The Missing Maps project aims to map the most vulnerable places in the world (affected by humanitarian crises: disease epidemics, conflict, natural disasters, poverty, environmental crises). Building on HOT's disaster preparedness projects, the Missing Maps tasks facilitate pre-emptive mapping of priority countries to better facilitate disaster response, medical activities and resource allocation when crises occur.

Thank you very much for mapping!
projectInfo.instructions:
##Instructions
**Imagery Note**
  *From the background menu please use  **Maxar Premium imagery**, also check Esri, Digital Globe, or Bing to compare
![Animated gif of changing background image in iD](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/61/Changing_background_settings_in_OpenStreetMap_ID_Editor.gif)
  * Cloud cover or resolution is often an issue in Tanzania, view several sources to ensure all buildings are identified
  * Please trace **buildings** from the satellite images.
  * We do not need other features like roads and landuse traced for this project
  * **Please do not trace over the top of existing buildings**
  * Some Task areas will not have buildings - This is ok and important information, please just mark them as "Completely Mapped" and select another Task Square. 
  * Most Commonly used tags:
**building=yes**
##Buildings
    * Please accurately outline all the buildings you can find. 
  * The outline should be for the full size of the building even if it is partly covered by trees in the imagery. Please do not generalize or stylize the building, the building size is used for population estimates, so please be as accurate as possible.
  * For square or rectangular buildings, after drawing the outline, **use the 'q' key in the web editor to "square" the corners**. -or- **right click on the building and choose the 'Square' option**
  * In the iD web editor, the first time you map a building you will use the "Building" category and then at the top of the list select "Building" again.
  * If the building already exists make sure it is square, but do not trace it again
  * Please do not snap the corners of buildings to other features such as roads and paths
**For rectangular buildings:** 
* In iD: draw an area and label it as “Building”, then correct for right angles with the “q” key.
![Animated gif of round building in iD](http://learnosm.org/images/hot-tips/rectangular_building.gif)
* In JOSM: To start drawing buildings, select the `B` key shortcut. For each bulding to add, we trace a line on one side of the building with two clicks then we slide the mouse to the opposite side of the building and we click to confirm adding the building. The tag “building=yes” is automatically traced.. To stop tracing buildings, we select the `S` shortcut. 

**For circular buildings:** 
* In iD: draw a triangular area over the building and use the tag "Building", then correct to make the shape circular with the "O" key.
![Animated gif of round building in iD](https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/w/images/8/80/Round-blds-id.gif)
* In JOSM: Select the `Ctrl-Alt-B` key shortcut  the show the `BuildingTools plugin` options and select the `Circle` option. The same shortcut is used to step back to the `Rectangle` option. For each round building, draw the diameter of the circle with two clicks on each side of the building. This automatically trace the building and the tag “building=yes” is added.. To stop tracing buildings, we select the `S` shortcut.

Thank you very much for mapping #missingmaps

Hi @[MariaCrv] , thank you! I fixed some buildings that were overlapping residential areas. If a residential area is in the way, you can adjust it by dragging a node or two to make room for the buildings you want to add. Some of the smaller buildings you added might just be bushes, zooming out a bit can often help to figure things out. But sometimes it is genuinely impossible to tell...! All good otherwise, thanks again :)

Thanks for mapping @[Misanya] ! I will reopen this task, as there are still buildings missing, and others need fixing. A few tips: make sure to always use the 'q' key to square the corners of buildings. Sometimes buildings can look off-square (because of the angle of the imagery, if trees are covering a part of the roof or because of reflections of a metal roof), but do draw them rectangular, the way they would be in reality. If what you've drawn is REALLY off-square, you will need to readjust the shape manually first to get closer to 90° angles, otherwise the 'q' key won't work. Buildings should not overlap other areas. If someone has added residential areas and they are in the way, you can move them a little to draw the buildings. I will send you a direct message with more info! Thanks again, and please keep mapping :)

Thanks for mapping @[MitchatSage] @[Atarimo] - please make sure to always use the 'q' key to square the corners of buildings. Before marking a task as done it is a good idea to use the issues tool: Resolving issues
Using the Issues tool on the right-hand side of the screen helps you to check your own and other mappers’ work before exiting the task. Type ‘i’ to open the menu. To find all unsquared buildings, change number to “up to 20°”  Thanks again and please keep mapping :)
